ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Is your child currently taking any medications?
Name of antidepressants other than SSRIs?
Dose of antidepressants other than SSRIs?

Notes: 1 = no effect; 2 =partial response; 3 =complete response; 4 = inadequate trial/ poor med tolerance/ unknown

ElementDescription: CCI question 25b: If 25=1, is currently taking medication for Parkinson's Disease;0=No,1=Yes
CCI question 15b: If 15=1, currently taking medication for diabetes/high blood sugar;0=No,1=Yes
Number of Medications to Treat Diabetes
Name of Medication for Treating Hypertension
